org.tms.api

Interface TableContext

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseElement, IndexableTableElements, InitializableTableProperties

    public interface TableContext
extends BaseElement, InitializableTableProperties
    A collection of Tables, initializable TablePropertys, and optional thread pools. Tables that share the same TableContext can reference one another in Column, Row, and Cell Derivations.

    See IndexableTableElements and InitializableTableProperties for additional methods that affect TableContexts.

    Since:
    "1.0"
    Version:
    "1.3"

      • getTable

        Table getTable(Access mode,
               java.lang.Object... mda)
        Returns the Table referenced by the Access specification and associated parameters. TableContext instances maintain a directory of the Table instances created within a given TableContext.
        Parameters:
        mode - the Access mode specified to reference the table
        mda - the associated Access mode parameters
        Returns:
        the referenced table
        Throws:
        InvalidAccessException - If Tables cannot be referenced using Access mode.
        InvalidException - If the Access additional parameters given in mda are not appropriate. See Access

      • loadDatabaseDriver

        default void loadDatabaseDriver(java.lang.String driverClassName)
                         throws java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Loads the JDBC database driver class named driverClassName and maintains an index of loaded class names.

        The default implementation throws UnsupportedImplementationException.

        Parameters:
        driverClassName - the JDBC driver class name to load
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - if the named JDBC driver class cannot be loaded
        UnsupportedImplementationException - if this method is called on a TableContext that uses the default implementation

        Registers a new BinaryOp Operator using the supplied BiFunction to compute the return value. As BiFunction is a FunctionalInterface, a lambda expression can be provided to perform the calculation.

        T - the class of the function's first argument
        U - the class of the function's second argument
        R - the class of the function's return type
        Parameters:

        argTypeX - the class of the first argument
        argTypeY - the class of the second argument
        resultType - the class of the return type

      • registerOperator

        void registerOperator(Operator oper)
        Registers the supplied Operator oper with this TableContext. Operators are used in Derivable expressions assigned to TableElements to perform calculations within the TMS Framework.
        Parameters:
        oper - the labeled Operator to register with this TableContext

      • deregisterOperator

        boolean deregisterOperator(Operator oper)
        Deregisters the supplied Operator oper from this TableContext.

        Note:Deregistering Operators only prevents them from being used as a new Derivable expression, it does not invalidate them in existing derivations.

        Parameters:
        oper - the Operator to deregister from this TableContext
        Returns:
        true if an Operator with the supplied label was found (and deregistered)

      • registerGroovyOperators

        void registerGroovyOperators(java.lang.String fileName)
        Loads and compiles the Groovy class contained in fileName. Operators are created from each public method that return a value found in the compiled class. The class itself must be concrete and instantiatable.
        Parameters:
        fileName - fully-qualified file name containing the Groovy class to compile and parse

      • registerGroovyOverload

        void registerGroovyOverload(java.lang.String label,
                            java.lang.Class<?> pType1,
                            java.lang.Class<?> pType2,
                            java.lang.Class<?> resultType,
                            java.lang.String fileName,
                            java.lang.String methodName)
        Registers a new BinaryOp Operator as an overloaded operator that uses the Groovy code specified in fileName to perform the calculation. Any valid Derivation operator, such as +, -, *, and / can be overloaded. Overloads take into account the class types of the participating operands to select the correct Operator to execute.
        Parameters:
        label - the overloaded operator name, which is used to reference this Operator in a Derivable expression
        pType1 - the class of the first operand
        pType2 - the class of the second operand
        resultType - the class of the return type
        fileName - fully-qualified file name containing the Groovy class containing the function logic
        methodName - the method name containing the Groovy code containing the function logic
